    "introSummary": "AI workflow automation matters when a business event needs interpretation and execution in the same process, such as a lead intake form submission that needs enrichment before a CRM update, a support ticket that needs classification and retrieval before a reply, or an invoice that needs extraction before writeback.\n\nGetForked helps define the workflow process, control points, system actions, and operating requirements, then matches you with an approved builder who can deliver an owned workflow with documentation, dashboards, and handover-ready logic.",
    "heroSummary": "AI workflow automation matters when a business event needs interpretation and execution in the same process, such as a lead intake form submission that needs enrichment before a CRM update, a support ticket that needs classification and retrieval before a reply, or an invoice that needs extraction before writeback.\n\nGetForked helps define the workflow process, control points, system actions, and operating requirements, then matches you with an approved builder who can deliver an owned workflow with documentation, dashboards, and handover-ready logic.",
    "problemSummary": "The risky part is not getting readable output from AI. The risky part is letting workflow process automation act on output that has not been checked against the real business process. A lead intake form submission may require company enrichment, duplicate detection, owner rules, and a valid CRM update payload before anything is written. A support ticket may require classification, knowledge-base retrieval, draft generation, and a status change that follows policy for refunds, escalations, or sensitive issues. An invoice or order workflow may extract the right-looking fields while still failing total checks, supplier matching, approval rules, or downstream writeback requirements.",
